    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1872-07-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1872-07-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="204" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d204">
                <head>No. 204.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hunter</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Francis</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                        of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1872-07-30">
                            <hi rend="italic">July</hi> 30,
                                1872</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 37.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Your dispatch numbered 67, under date of
                            the 3d Instant, inclosing correspondence relative to the rumored
                            shipment of Greek criminals to the United States, is received, and the
                            communication which you addressed upon that subject to the
                            secretary-general is approved. The contradiction which has been given by
                            the government of Greece to the rumor referred to, as communicated in
                            your dispatch No. 63, was, upon the receipt of that dispatch, sent to
                            the press for publication.</p>
                <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>W. HUNTER,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
